# Vue Component Guidelines

## Required: defineOptions

Every SFC **must** declare `defineOptions` with `name` matching the PascalCase filename — place it before `ref`, `computed`, or any other composable calls:

```ts
defineOptions({ name: 'MyComponent' })
```

## Props

Always define props through a local `IProps` interface. Types must come from `~/types/index` via an explicit `type` import:

```ts
import type { IInterviewSection } from '~/types/index'

interface IProps {
  section: IInterviewSection
  index: number
}

const props = defineProps<IProps>()
```

Never use runtime `defineProps({ ... })` with inline type literals.

## Script Setup

- **`async/await` only** — no `.then()` chains
- **`try/catch` with `err: unknown`** — narrow the error inside the block; never `catch (err: any)`
- **Explicit type annotations** on every `ref`, `computed`, and function signature — no rely-on-inference for public APIs
- **No one-line conditions** — always use braces, even for single-statement bodies

## Template

- Prefer `v-for` with an explicit `:key` that is not an array index when working with `IInterviewGuide` / `IInterviewSection` / `IInterviewQuestion` — use `.id`
- Use `v-bind` shorthand (`:prop`) and `v-on` shorthand (`@event`)
- Never call complex logic inline in templates — extract to a `computed` or method

## SCSS (always scoped + BEM)

Every component ends with `<style scoped lang="scss">`. Use BEM:

```scss
.question-card { // block
  &__header { ... }     // element
  &__header--active { ... } // modifier
}
```

Import design tokens from `~/assets/scss/_variables.scss` via `@use` if needed. Never hardcode colors or spacing values directly — use the CSS variables defined in `global.scss` (e.g. `var(--color-accent)`, `var(--gap-md)`).

## Canonical Examples

- **Simple component**: `app/components/InterviewSection.vue` — single prop, minimal state, no async
- **Complex component**: `app/components/QuestionCard.vue` — expand/collapse state, rich markdown/code rendering, `useInterviewGuide` composable usage
- **Page component**: `app/pages/interview/[id].vue` — route param, `onMounted` data load, full guide rendering

## Composable Usage

Use `useInterviewGuide()` for all guide state, history, and label/color helpers. Never duplicate its logic inline:

```ts
const { result, isLoading, error, generate, loadGuide, categoryColor, providerLabel } = useInterviewGuide()
```

Use `useDateFormat()` for any date/time display — never call `new Date().toLocaleString()` directly in components.
